OL,3,CA&E charges risk people avoiding vital
OL,4,Cmedical services, says charity
OL,6,FHowever, the island's Health Minister,
OL,7,FDeputy Tom Binet, says he does not
OL,8,Fbelieve this will be the case.
OL,10,F"The idea isn't that you have to not
OL,11,Fturn up to A&E", he says.
OL,13,F"If you turn up to A&E with something
OL,14,Fthat should've gone to a GP for you
OL,15,Fcan still get treatment - but you have
OL,16,Fto pay for it in the same way as you
OL,17,Fwould at the GP."
OL,19,FHowever, Deputy Binet also adds the
OL,20,Fcharge "isn't about raising revenue -
OL,21,Fit's about changing behaviours".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/12
